From: hmaarrfk <mark.harfouche@conda-forge.org>
Date: 2026-06-04
Subject: npu_compiler: drop WEIGHTLESS_BLOB (removed from OpenVINO 2026.2)

vcl_compiler.cpp gates the weight-separated ("weightless") compile path
on either intel_npu::ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS or intel_npu::WEIGHTLESS_BLOB. As
its own comment states, "WEIGHTLESS_BLOB is equivalent with
ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS [...] accepting both to facilitate the transition to
ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS." The npu_ud_2026_20 tag was developed against an
OpenVINO commit still mid-transition that defined both options.

The public OpenVINO 2026.2.0 release we build against has finished that
transition: it defines only ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS (config/options.hpp) and
no longer provides WEIGHTLESS_BLOB, so the two runtime references fail:

    vcl_compiler.cpp:410: error: 'WEIGHTLESS_BLOB' is not a member of
      'intel_npu'

Since the two options are documented as equivalent, drop the
WEIGHTLESS_BLOB half of each guard and key the weightless path solely on
ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS. (The only other use, an _options->add<WEIGHTLESS_BLOB>
registration, is under #ifdef VPUX_DEVELOPER_BUILD, which this packaging
build does not define, so it is left untouched.)

--- a/src/vpux_driver_compiler/src/vpux_compiler_l0/vcl_compiler.cpp
+++ b/src/vpux_driver_compiler/src/vpux_compiler_l0/vcl_compiler.cpp
@@ -406,8 +406,7 @@
             // WEIGHTLESS_BLOB is equivalent with ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS
             // Accepting both to facilitate the transition to ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS
             const auto compiler = _compilerLoader->getCompiler();
-            if (buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS>() ||
-                buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::WEIGHTLESS_BLOB>()) {
+            if (buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS>()) {
                 return compiler->compileWsIterative(model, buildInfo.parsedConfig,
                                                     buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::WS_COMPILE_CALL_NUMBER>());
             }
@@ -452,8 +451,7 @@
         // WEIGHTLESS_BLOB is equivalent with ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS
         // Accepting both to facilitate the transition to ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS
         const auto compiler = _compilerLoader->getCompiler();
-        if (buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS>() ||
-            buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::WEIGHTLESS_BLOB>()) {
+        if (buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::ENABLE_WEIGHTLESS>()) {
             return compiler->compileWsIterative(model, buildInfo.parsedConfig,
                                                 buildInfo.parsedConfig.get<intel_npu::WS_COMPILE_CALL_NUMBER>(),
                                                 allocator);
